Apply an arbitrary function to video frames.  

Function can be filter, blob detector, etc., or a combination of multiple 
functions.

Function must take 3d numpy ndarrays as input and return 2d or 3d numpy arrays

Sample video 'test.mpg' is taken from open-video.org and is titled 'NASA 25th
Anniversary Show, Segment 01'  

Code has been updated to support Python 3.4+ and OpenCV 3.0.
Earlier versions of either may not be supported.
See first commit for use with python 2 and earlier opencv versions

